<%= section "Add a new course to OpenStax Tutor" do %> 

<p>Before an instructor can register to teach a class, the class must be listed in the Course Catalog <em>and</em> the instructor must be added as an approved instructor.</p>

<p>If your class is not listed in the Course Catalog, follow the steps below.</p>
  
  <ol>
    <li>Ensure that you have already created an OST account;</li>
    <li>Contact OpenStax Tutor administrators (EMAIL) and provide the following information:</li>
    <ul>
      <li>Full course name, e.g. Math 101: Single-Variable Calculus;</li>
      <li>Short course name, e.g. Math 101;</li>
      <li>Brief description of the course;</li>
      <li>When class is typically offered, e.g. Fall or Spring; and</li>
      <li>Instructor's OpenStax Tutor username, i.e. username he/she uses to log in to the site.</li>
    </ul>
    <li>Once the administrator has added your course to the catalog and has added you as an instructor, you are ready to register to teach this course. Go here.</li>
  </ol>

  <% end %>